1
00:00:08,467 --> 00:00:11,000
<i>I've decided
who Paradiso Escaño's</i>

2
00:00:11,133 --> 00:00:16,433
<i>exclusive realty partner will be
the Torrecampo Realty.</i>

3
00:00:16,567 --> 00:00:17,900
<i> Your shoulder's dislocated.</i>

4
00:00:18,033 --> 00:00:19,200
<i> Must've gotten hit earlier.</i>

5
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:20,733
<i>Let's get a drink,
it'll numb the pain.</i>

6
00:00:20,867 --> 00:00:23,433
<i>I just want
to lose control right now.</i>

7
00:00:23,567 --> 00:00:26,300
<i>Edward, why don't you just give
your brother</i>

8
00:00:26,433 --> 00:00:27,800
<i> the benefit of the doubt.</i>

9
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:30,633
<i>and focus on how you're going
to court</i>

10
00:00:30,767 --> 00:00:32,433
<i> Marj when they get back?</i>

11
00:00:32,567 --> 00:00:34,033
<i> You don't owe me anything.</i>

12
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,767
<i>I'll forget what happened
between us.</i>

13
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:36,633
<i> Just like you want.</i>

14
00:00:36,767 --> 00:00:37,967
<i>Mom's going out for a bit, okay?</i>

15
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:39,133
<i> But I'll be back soon.</i>

16
00:00:39,267 --> 00:00:40,567
<i> Where did my mom go?</i>

17
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:43,600
<i>If your sister calls,
don't say anything, alright?</i>

18
00:00:43,733 --> 00:00:44,900
<i> Beats me, when I got here,</i>

19
00:00:45,033 --> 00:00:46,033
<i> she was already gone.</i>

20
00:00:46,167 --> 00:00:48,667
<i>Even Jobert stayed up all night
waiting for her!</i>

21
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:51,900
Thank you, Miss Rona.

22
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:53,533
If you see Mom,

23
00:00:53,667 --> 00:00:56,200
please call or text me
right away.

24
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:57,967
Okay, thanks so much.

25
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:02,300
I already reported to the police
that Auntie Evelyn is missing.

26
00:01:03,267 --> 00:01:05,267
Do you have any idea
where she might've gone?

27
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:07,567
I can't think of anywhere
right now.

28
00:01:12,300 --> 00:01:14,500
Mom!

29
00:01:14,633 --> 00:01:17,167
I'm going crazy worrying about
what happened to you.

30
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:18,933
Where have you been?

31
00:01:19,067 --> 00:01:21,800
And I told you
not to leave Jobert alone.

32
00:01:21,933 --> 00:01:25,100
Mom, I told you to watch Jobert.

33
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:27,733
Dear, I just couldn't
help myself

34
00:01:27,867 --> 00:01:29,400
I had to talk to him.

35
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,600
Who?

36
00:01:32,667 --> 00:01:33,867
Mom, I don't understand.

37
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,933
Who are you talking about?

38
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:40,433
Ah, Marj,

39
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,633
my child.

40
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:40,033
What is he doing here?

41
00:02:41,867 --> 00:02:45,967
Your dad and I talked, Marj.

42
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:47,233
We decided

43
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:50,700
to give our relationship
another chance.

44
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:52,067
Mom!

45
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:54,500
Are you falling for it again?

46
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:58,500
Marj, it's not like that.

47
00:02:58,633 --> 00:02:59,867
Your father has changed.

48
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,633
Mom! That's the same old story!

49
00:03:02,767 --> 00:03:04,500
He always pretends he's changed,

50
00:03:04,633 --> 00:03:06,700
but we all know how this ends!

51
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:08,700
Marj, please listen first.

52
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,433
I almost got mugged last night.

53
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:13,633
My phone even got destroyed.

54
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,333
If it weren't for your dad,

55
00:03:15,467 --> 00:03:17,567
who knows what would've
happened to me.

56
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:21,933
Dear, I promised your mom
I'd be better.

57
00:03:23,133 --> 00:03:27,433
I'll make it up to her
and to you and Jobert.

58
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,433
Please, give me one more chance

59
00:03:30,567 --> 00:03:33,700
to prove I can be
your father again.

60
00:03:33,833 --> 00:03:36,500
- Please, my child.
- Please, sweetheart.

61
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:38,767
He's just gonna fool you again.

62
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:40,733
Mom, use your head for once!

63
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:42,833
Stop letting your emotions
run everything!

64
00:03:42,967 --> 00:03:44,000
Marj.

65
00:03:44,133 --> 00:03:45,833
Don't raise your voice
at your mother like that.

66
00:03:45,967 --> 00:03:47,533
Don't tell me what to do!

67
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:50,433
You lost that right after
what you did to us!

68
00:03:50,567 --> 00:03:51,867
Noise.

69
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:56,233
- Noise! Noise! Noise!
- Marj!

70
00:03:57,567 --> 00:03:58,867
Mom!

71
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,400
Mom!

72
00:04:02,533 --> 00:04:03,400
So loud!

73
00:04:03,533 --> 00:04:06,000
Jobert. wait.
Please just leave!

74
00:04:06,133 --> 00:04:07,900
Stop bothering us!

75
00:04:08,033 --> 00:04:11,100
Enough! Stop messing
with my mom's head!

76
00:04:11,233 --> 00:04:12,467
We don't need you!

77
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:14,167
Get out!

78
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:17,467
So loud!

79
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:22,667
- Lito!
- Mom!

80
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,033
Mom!

81
00:04:24,167 --> 00:04:25,767
Noise!

82
00:04:32,233 --> 00:04:33,600
Mom!

83
00:04:50,567 --> 00:04:52,500
Manang, how is he?

84
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:55,500
He's still upset...

85
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:59,900
because Sir Greg sent you
to Batangas instead of him.

86
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,533
Bro, how'd your...

87
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,833
meeting with Mr. Fuentes go?

88
00:05:29,967 --> 00:05:33,000
How is it?
Did you close the deal?

89
00:05:33,133 --> 00:05:34,900
I was calling you last night.

90
00:05:35,067 --> 00:05:36,500
You didn't answer.

91
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:38,967
Sorry, I didn't hear it.

92
00:05:42,167 --> 00:05:46,200
Marj was drunk
when I talked to her.

93
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:47,633
And I heard you.

94
00:05:49,633 --> 00:05:51,333
You offered to take her
to her room.

95
00:05:52,133 --> 00:05:55,733
I couldn't just
leave her there, could I?

96
00:05:57,067 --> 00:05:58,100
And then what?

97
00:06:00,433 --> 00:06:02,233
What do you mean, "then what"?

98
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,300
You undressed her?

99
00:06:04,433 --> 00:06:06,033
You laid her down?

100
00:06:06,167 --> 00:06:07,300
You kissed her?

101
00:06:10,233 --> 00:06:11,600
Dude...

102
00:06:11,733 --> 00:06:12,533
your mind's filthy.

103
00:06:12,667 --> 00:06:14,100
When did you start
thinking that way?

104
00:06:15,533 --> 00:06:16,967
Paolo, I know you.

105
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,233
I know how you are with women.

106
00:06:20,367 --> 00:06:22,000
Just tell me the truth.

107
00:06:22,133 --> 00:06:23,867
Did something happen
between you and Marj?

108
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,333
Don't try
to say anything, Paolo.

109
00:06:32,467 --> 00:06:33,767
Just don't.

110
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:41,367
You told me
you didn't like her!

111
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:43,700
You said I should go for her!

112
00:06:45,067 --> 00:06:47,067
I was about to tell Marj
I liked her!

113
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,000
Then what?
What did you do?

114
00:06:49,133 --> 00:06:51,500
You had to try her out first
before handing her over to me?

115
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:12,333
Good job, Paolo.

116
00:07:12,467 --> 00:07:16,433
Glad I trusted my gut
and sent you to Batangas.

117
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,133
Actually, Dad, you should be
congratulating Marj.

118
00:07:19,267 --> 00:07:20,700
If it weren't for her,

119
00:07:20,833 --> 00:07:22,467
we wouldn't have closed
the deal.

120
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,300
I was wrong about her.

121
00:07:25,433 --> 00:07:28,533
I thought she'd just be trouble.

122
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:31,800
But now, I can see
she has a great potentials.

123
00:07:31,933 --> 00:07:34,567
Mr. Escaño said the same thing.

124
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:35,733
He believes in her.

125
00:07:35,867 --> 00:07:39,633
She's not just pretty,
smart and, capable.

126
00:07:39,767 --> 00:07:40,833
She's also kind.

127
00:07:40,967 --> 00:07:42,800
Yes, Marj's kind.

128
00:07:42,933 --> 00:07:44,333
And too trusting.

129
00:07:44,467 --> 00:07:46,933
That's why people
take advantage of her.

130
00:07:47,067 --> 00:07:48,700
Like who?

131
00:07:56,167 --> 00:07:57,267
<i> Please have mercy on us</i>

132
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,367
<i>- for our child.
- Mom!</i>

133
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:01,133
<i> For our kids' sake, Lito.</i>

134
00:08:01,267 --> 00:08:02,833
<i> We have nowhere else to go.</i>

135
00:08:02,967 --> 00:08:05,900
<i> Please have mercy on us, Lito.</i>

136
00:08:06,033 --> 00:08:07,367
<i> I don't need them!</i>

137
00:08:10,633 --> 00:08:13,200
<i>Ever since your father
and I separated,</i>

138
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:15,400
<i> I became weak, sweetheart.</i>

139
00:08:16,633 --> 00:08:18,200
<i> Please forgive me.</i>

140
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:28,067
Sis?

141
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,600
Are you okay?

142
00:08:30,633 --> 00:08:32,200
I don't understand.

143
00:08:33,733 --> 00:08:36,167
I really don't understand
my mom.

144
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:40,467
Instead of helping me
build a life,

145
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:43,700
she brings trouble back
into this house.

146
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:47,033
I already told her
not to take him back.

147
00:08:47,167 --> 00:08:48,033
But what can we do?

148
00:08:48,167 --> 00:08:49,967
Your mom's just really weak.

149
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:53,967
How many times do I have
to tell her that?

150
00:08:55,467 --> 00:08:56,667
It's exhausting.

151
00:08:57,733 --> 00:08:59,733
I'm the one holding
everything together.

152
00:08:59,867 --> 00:09:01,133
Me, always me.

153
00:09:01,267 --> 00:09:03,400
Everyone depends on me,

154
00:09:03,533 --> 00:09:06,533
and I'm not made of stone.

155
00:09:07,667 --> 00:09:10,100
I get tired, too.

156
00:09:10,233 --> 00:09:11,433
I know.

157
00:09:11,567 --> 00:09:13,567
Nothing about this is easy.

158
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:17,367
Hey, can we talk
about something else?

159
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:19,467
Anything but Marj,
okay? Please?

160
00:09:21,467 --> 00:09:23,333
It's rare that I get impressed.

161
00:09:23,467 --> 00:09:25,200
My standards are high.

162
00:09:25,633 --> 00:09:28,200
But Marj?

163
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:29,467
She's approved.

164
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:32,167
That's the kind of woman
you should be dating, son.

165
00:09:34,067 --> 00:09:36,200
You two will make a great pair.

166
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:57,967
Excuse me.

167
00:09:58,100 --> 00:10:00,500
This is for Ms. Marj Castillo.

168
00:10:00,633 --> 00:10:03,433
Ah, that's sweet!

169
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,900
Who's it from?

170
00:10:13,767 --> 00:10:17,733
<i>What happened between us
wasn't nothing to me.</i>

171
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:19,733
<i>I know you're going through
something right now.</i>

172
00:10:19,867 --> 00:10:22,167
<i>and I hope everything works out.</i>

173
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:24,433
<i>I just want you to know that
I'm thinking of you.</i>

174
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:26,567
<i> I'm just here.</i>

175
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:57,833
Jobert.

176
00:10:57,967 --> 00:10:59,967
Why is my little brother
so quiet?

177
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,933
Sorry, Sis.

178
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:07,933
What for?

179
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:11,767
You and Mom are fighting.

180
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:14,200
I don't know how to fix it.

181
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:18,433
I'm sorry, Jobert.

182
00:11:19,367 --> 00:11:22,000
Sorry, you're stuck
between Mom and me.

183
00:11:23,867 --> 00:11:25,300
I'm sorry.

184
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:29,233
I don't want to fight
with her either.

185
00:11:29,367 --> 00:11:32,967
But if I don't say anything,

186
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:35,367
she'll be the one who gets hurt
in the end.

187
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,133
Jobert, don't worry
about it, okay?

188
00:11:42,033 --> 00:11:44,100
What matters is

189
00:11:44,233 --> 00:11:46,200
I love you.

190
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:47,300
Okay?

191
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:50,300
I love you too, Sis.

192
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:51,667
Sorry.

193
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:53,700
It's okay.

194
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:57,400
Sorry.

195
00:11:59,367 --> 00:12:00,633
Mom, wait.

196
00:12:00,767 --> 00:12:03,000
Don't tell me you're leaving.

197
00:12:04,033 --> 00:12:05,200
I am, Marj.

198
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:10,700
I want to give your father
another chance.

199
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:14,267
I want this family
to be whole again.

200
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,567
If you can't accept him,

201
00:12:16,733 --> 00:12:19,633
then Jobert and I will leave
this house.

202
00:12:20,933 --> 00:12:22,567
Mom, are you serious?

203
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,133
Yes.

204
00:12:24,267 --> 00:12:29,100
Because I feel like
I have no freedom here.

205
00:12:30,433 --> 00:12:32,767
No right to be happy.

206
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:34,933
No right to love.

207
00:12:35,067 --> 00:12:37,200
Mom, what did I do wrong?

208
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:40,233
All I did was care!

209
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:44,567
If there's anyone here who's
been unhappy her whole life,

210
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:45,933
it's me!

211
00:12:46,067 --> 00:12:48,967
I never got to enjoy my youth.

212
00:12:49,133 --> 00:12:51,567
I sacrificed everything for you,

213
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:53,600
and now I'm the bad one?

214
00:12:54,633 --> 00:12:56,733
If you can't live without Dad,
then leave!

215
00:12:56,867 --> 00:12:59,100
But don't take my brother!

216
00:12:59,233 --> 00:13:00,867
Jobert is your father's son.

217
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,633
He's our son.

218
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:03,633
I'm taking Jobert!

219
00:13:03,767 --> 00:13:05,667
Mom, didn't you see yesterday?

220
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:08,067
He didn't even go near Jobert!

221
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,833
Because you kicked him out!

222
00:13:09,967 --> 00:13:11,300
Mom, come on!

223
00:13:11,433 --> 00:13:15,333
Seriously! Did you forget
how he hurt Jobert?

224
00:13:15,467 --> 00:13:18,500
How he said Jobert
wasn't even his kid?

225
00:13:18,633 --> 00:13:21,000
Because he couldn't accept that
Jobert is different!

226
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:26,467
Mom, don't leave.

227
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,900
- I don't want.
- Jobert.

228
00:13:28,033 --> 00:13:30,867
- I don't want, I don't want.
- Let Mom go.

229
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,400
- I don't want.
- Let Mom go.

230
00:13:32,533 --> 00:13:34,333
I don't want Mom to leave!

231
00:13:34,467 --> 00:13:35,333
She chose Dad.

232
00:13:35,467 --> 00:13:37,167
- Let Mom go.
- No, I don't want.

233
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:38,633
Mom...

234
00:13:38,767 --> 00:13:40,400
- I don't want Mom to leave!
- If that's how she wants

235
00:13:40,533 --> 00:13:43,233
to get treated,
then let her leave!

236
00:13:43,367 --> 00:13:45,533
Don't take my brother!

237
00:13:45,667 --> 00:13:48,433
No...

238
00:13:48,567 --> 00:13:50,033
Mom...

239
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:56,833
Mom! Mom!

240
00:14:00,233 --> 00:14:02,633
Jobert, stay here.

241
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:16,267
Mom!

242
00:14:20,233 --> 00:14:25,767
Mom!

243
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:29,567
Here, here,
just a little more.

244
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:31,067
That's it, just a bit.

245
00:14:33,667 --> 00:14:34,633
Very good.

246
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:37,767
Where's Mom?

247
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:39,667
Jobert misses Mom.

248
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:43,800
I miss her.

249
00:14:44,933 --> 00:14:47,300
I miss Mom, too, Jobert.

250
00:14:47,433 --> 00:14:49,800
Don't worry,
she'll be back soon.

251
00:14:51,933 --> 00:14:55,167
How about I buy you a turtle
keychain later?

252
00:14:56,733 --> 00:14:57,667
Turtle keychain!

253
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,867
Jobert wants!
Just like Pong!

254
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,733
Pong.

255
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:06,133
Girl, thank you.

256
00:15:06,267 --> 00:15:09,133
Thanks for helping me
take care of Jobert.

257
00:15:09,267 --> 00:15:12,033
I'll be back right
after my presentation.

258
00:15:12,167 --> 00:15:13,333
I should be here by lunchtime.

259
00:15:13,467 --> 00:15:14,833
Yeah. Sis, we've got
a big problem.

260
00:15:14,967 --> 00:15:17,400
Sir Greg called me. He wants me
to edit the presentation.

261
00:15:17,533 --> 00:15:19,267
But it's all
on the office computer.

262
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:20,333
I can't do anything about it.

263
00:15:20,467 --> 00:15:21,300
I won't be able to watch
Jobert this morning.

264
00:15:21,433 --> 00:15:22,300
- I'm sorry.
- Hey, hey, sis.

265
00:15:22,433 --> 00:15:23,800
Relax.

266
00:15:23,933 --> 00:15:25,167
Just relax.

267
00:15:26,433 --> 00:15:29,167
I'll just file for emergency
leave later.

268
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:30,267
What?

269
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:32,867
You have big time client.

270
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:34,333
That's a big account, right?

271
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:35,600
What if they give it
to someone else?

272
00:15:35,733 --> 00:15:37,033
That'd be such a waste.

273
00:15:37,167 --> 00:15:39,733
If only they would give it
to me, then that would be great.

274
00:15:54,933 --> 00:15:56,800
Remember this place, Jobert?

275
00:15:58,267 --> 00:16:00,267
Look, there's Hannah.

276
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,833
- Hey, Jobert.
- And there's Mikee.

277
00:16:04,433 --> 00:16:05,967
Come on, sit here for now.

278
00:16:07,267 --> 00:16:08,433
There you go.

279
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:10,267
There.

280
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:12,233
Oops.

281
00:16:12,367 --> 00:16:14,567
Here, watch this
for a bit, okay?

282
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:17,567
While I talk to someone.

283
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:22,367
- Behave, all right?
- Girl...

284
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:23,733
it's 9 o'clock,
your client.

285
00:16:23,867 --> 00:16:24,733
Oh, right.

286
00:16:24,867 --> 00:16:26,267
Can you watch Jobert for me
for now?

287
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,567
Yes, I've got him.

288
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:28,567
Thanks.

289
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:30,133
Bye, Jobert.

290
00:16:30,267 --> 00:16:31,200
Stay right here, okay?

291
00:16:31,333 --> 00:16:32,833
Behave.

292
00:16:32,967 --> 00:16:34,267
Here.

293
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:38,833
And this house in Tagaytay,

294
00:16:38,967 --> 00:16:41,467
it has three bedrooms
and three bathrooms

295
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:45,600
with a 360 degree view,
and it is safe for kids.

296
00:16:45,767 --> 00:16:47,767
You have two children, right?

297
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:48,867
That's right.

298
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:52,300
I'm glad you're considering
my kids.

299
00:16:52,433 --> 00:16:53,433
Of course, Ma'am.

300
00:16:53,567 --> 00:16:56,933
That's why we build good homes
for our families.

301
00:17:10,967 --> 00:17:14,000
What's the total floor area
of the property?

302
00:17:20,567 --> 00:17:21,967
Is everything okay?

303
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:23,467
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

304
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:26,233
My younger brother doesn't have
a babysitter today,

305
00:17:26,367 --> 00:17:28,067
and I'm the only one with him.

306
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:31,300
He has autism, so I'm worried.

307
00:17:37,667 --> 00:17:39,233
Anyway, the total floor area...

308
00:17:39,367 --> 00:17:42,167
Ah! We don't have to do this
right now

309
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:44,733
if your brother needs you.

310
00:17:44,867 --> 00:17:46,433
I understand.

311
00:17:46,567 --> 00:17:50,033
I'm a single mom
with little kids,

312
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:53,600
and I'm the breadwinner, too.

313
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:59,000
Then you know how hard
it is to juggle work and family.

314
00:17:59,767 --> 00:18:01,133
Of course.

315
00:18:01,267 --> 00:18:02,667
It's really hard

316
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:05,567
when you have no one to share
the responsibility with.

317
00:18:06,633 --> 00:18:08,900
So, let's just reschedule?

318
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:11,833
Ah, how about Wednesday
afternoon?

319
00:18:13,167 --> 00:18:14,333
Yes, yes.

320
00:18:14,467 --> 00:18:15,767
Thank you so much, Ma'am.

321
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:17,500
Ah, I'll go ahead now.

322
00:18:17,633 --> 00:18:18,867
Thank you.

323
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,200
Thank you.

324
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:22,600
Sorry.

325
00:18:32,933 --> 00:18:34,133
Jobert?

326
00:18:35,767 --> 00:18:37,167
Oh my god.

327
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:40,900
Jobert?

328
00:18:41,033 --> 00:18:43,300
Gi, did you see my brother?

329
00:18:43,433 --> 00:18:45,633
No, I didn't,
I just got back.

330
00:18:46,733 --> 00:18:48,600
Cindy, Cindy!

331
00:18:48,733 --> 00:18:50,000
Did you see my brother?

332
00:18:50,133 --> 00:18:52,800
Sorry, Marj,
I just came from a meeting.

333
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:59,000
Mikee! Did you see my brother?

334
00:18:59,133 --> 00:19:01,200
it's Jobert.

335
00:19:01,333 --> 00:19:02,200
No, I didn't see him.

336
00:19:02,333 --> 00:19:03,133
Are you sure?

337
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:05,367
Hannah left him here earlier.

338
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:07,133
I really didn't see him.

339
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:14,067
Jobert?

340
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:16,267
- Jobert!
- I feel bad for that teenager.

341
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:18,000
It's awful,
there's so much blood.

342
00:19:18,133 --> 00:19:19,400
I wonder how he is.

343
00:19:21,033 --> 00:19:22,367
Jobert!

344
00:19:35,933 --> 00:19:37,133
<i> Sis!</i>

345
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:40,400
Jobert.

346
00:19:40,533 --> 00:19:41,967
Sis!

347
00:19:44,833 --> 00:19:47,667
My god, I thought you were
the one who got hit.

348
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:49,267
Ah, sorry.
I was trying to call you.

349
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:52,067
I saw Jobert walking alone
in the hallway.

350
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:55,933
Kind Big Bro bought me
ice cream!

351
00:19:56,067 --> 00:19:57,133
Yummy!

352
00:19:57,267 --> 00:19:58,633
- Look, look!
- Jobert, I told you

353
00:19:58,767 --> 00:20:00,733
not to leave my desk.

354
00:20:01,933 --> 00:20:04,000
I finished watching the videos.

355
00:20:04,133 --> 00:20:05,700
I got bored.

356
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:11,933
Paolo, thank you.

357
00:20:13,033 --> 00:20:14,533
And sorry if I scared you.

358
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:18,567
I thought he'd get less agitated
if we got some air and a snack.

359
00:20:18,700 --> 00:20:20,400
And it turns out
he loves ice cream.

360
00:20:20,533 --> 00:20:21,800
Oh, Jobert.

361
00:20:21,933 --> 00:20:27,100
Anyone who doesn't like ice
cream isn't normal.

362
00:20:29,967 --> 00:20:31,667
Well, I hope that guy is okay.

363
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:34,700
That's why, Jobert,

364
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:37,467
don't cross the street
by yourself, okay?

365
00:20:37,633 --> 00:20:39,000
Okay.

366
00:20:42,033 --> 00:20:44,000
Ice cream.

367
00:20:44,133 --> 00:20:45,800
Ice cream.

368
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:58,733
- Heading home now, Jobert?
- Kind Big Brother.

369
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:03,533
Thank you again for finding
Jobert earlier.

370
00:21:03,667 --> 00:21:06,000
If you hadn't, something bad
could've happened.

371
00:21:06,133 --> 00:21:07,633
I know he'll be fine.

372
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:09,167
Jobert's tough, right?

373
00:21:10,267 --> 00:21:11,300
Jobert strong!

374
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:18,900
Why are you smiling?

375
00:21:21,167 --> 00:21:22,233
Nothing.

376
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:23,967
Come on, tell me.

377
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:29,800
A lot happened today,

378
00:21:29,933 --> 00:21:31,533
but for some reason,

379
00:21:31,667 --> 00:21:34,367
it doesn't feel as heavy.

380
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,567
Thanks, by the way,

381
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:38,600
for being Jobert's
babysitter for a bit.

382
00:21:40,567 --> 00:21:42,067
Kidding.

383
00:21:42,233 --> 00:21:45,133
You know, sometimes
you just have to admit

384
00:21:45,267 --> 00:21:47,767
to yourself that you need help.

385
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:50,267
I know you're Miss Tough Girl.

386
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:53,200
But you get tired, too, right?

387
00:21:54,367 --> 00:21:55,667
You're right.

388
00:21:56,767 --> 00:22:00,600
So this is what it feels like
to have someone share the load.

389
00:22:00,733 --> 00:22:04,333
Someone who helps
without being asked,

390
00:22:04,467 --> 00:22:08,767
given willingly
out of good intentions.

391
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:11,067
Even if it's not obvious.

392
00:22:16,100 --> 00:22:19,200
- Oh.
- Sis, message.

393
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:26,500
<i>Marj, can we talk for a moment?</i>

394
00:22:27,567 --> 00:22:29,533
I got a message from Edward.

395
00:22:29,667 --> 00:22:31,433
He wants to talk.

396
00:22:32,667 --> 00:22:34,500
Go, talk to him.

397
00:22:34,633 --> 00:22:35,933
That's important.

398
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:39,800
Do you know what this is about?

399
00:22:39,933 --> 00:22:41,200
I have an idea,

400
00:22:41,333 --> 00:22:43,967
but I don't want to assume.

401
00:22:52,467 --> 00:22:54,367
You sure you don't want
to go inside?

402
00:22:54,500 --> 00:22:55,600
No, it's okay.

403
00:22:56,333 --> 00:22:58,600
It's actually better out here.

404
00:22:58,733 --> 00:23:00,033
No one can hear us.

405
00:23:01,233 --> 00:23:02,733
Are you okay?

406
00:23:02,867 --> 00:23:04,600
You don't look like it.

407
00:23:04,733 --> 00:23:06,400
Sorry.

408
00:23:06,533 --> 00:23:07,733
Is it obvious?

409
00:23:09,700 --> 00:23:12,200
Is this because you
and your brother fought?

410
00:23:15,433 --> 00:23:16,600
How did you know?

411
00:23:18,500 --> 00:23:21,333
He didn't tell me everything.

412
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:25,867
But Paolo said you two
had a disagreement.

413
00:23:30,433 --> 00:23:31,767
I'll be honest with you.

414
00:23:32,867 --> 00:23:34,667
It's not just
a misunderstanding.

415
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,433
I'm really mad at Paolo.

416
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:40,000
He admitted to me that something
happened between you two

417
00:23:40,133 --> 00:23:41,433
- in Batangas.
- What?

418
00:23:41,567 --> 00:23:43,067
What?

419
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:45,200
- He told you that?
- Yes, he did.

420
00:23:46,533 --> 00:23:48,733
To tell you the truth, I've...

421
00:23:48,867 --> 00:23:51,133
I've felt so betrayed.

422
00:23:51,267 --> 00:23:53,033
Because Paolo knows that...

423
00:23:54,833 --> 00:23:55,967
I like you.

424
00:23:59,500 --> 00:24:00,533
What?

425
00:24:03,567 --> 00:24:05,267
Marj, I like you.

426
00:24:14,067 --> 00:24:15,500
Edward, are you serious?

427
00:24:18,233 --> 00:24:19,433
I am.

428
00:24:21,133 --> 00:24:22,233
I like you.

429
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:28,200
That's why it hurts seeing you
fall for Paolo.

430
00:24:29,133 --> 00:24:30,767
What was that?
Did he get you drunk

431
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:32,400
on purpose just to take
advantage of you?

432
00:24:32,533 --> 00:24:33,833
No, no,
that's not it.

433
00:24:33,967 --> 00:24:36,333
No, we both wanted it.

434
00:24:36,467 --> 00:24:39,067
But it didn't mean anything.

435
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:40,567
That's exactly
what he wants you to see.

436
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:42,767
That's exactly
what he wants you to believe.

437
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:43,767
That it was nothing.

438
00:24:43,900 --> 00:24:45,500
That you shouldn't
expect anything.

439
00:24:46,467 --> 00:24:47,900
That's just how Paolo is.

440
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:51,433
He'll do whatever it takes
to make you like him.

441
00:24:51,567 --> 00:24:53,000
And in the end,

442
00:24:53,133 --> 00:24:55,233
he'll just leave.

443
00:24:55,367 --> 00:24:57,267
He'll let go.

444
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:58,967
And you're the one who gets hurt
in the end.

445
00:24:59,100 --> 00:25:00,633
That's the kind of guy he is.

446
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:08,033
But the Paolo I saw
in Batangas was different.

447
00:25:08,933 --> 00:25:10,533
I got to know him better.

448
00:25:11,500 --> 00:25:13,300
Marj, don't let him fool you.

449
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:16,967
He's not a good guy.

450
00:25:17,100 --> 00:25:18,133
Look, he already blabbed to me

451
00:25:18,267 --> 00:25:19,100
about what happened
between you two.

452
00:25:19,233 --> 00:25:20,133
Who knows?

453
00:25:20,267 --> 00:25:22,400
who else he'll tell?

454
00:25:34,500 --> 00:25:35,700
But me...

455
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:39,500
I'm serious about you.

456
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:43,600
I'm serious about how I feel.

457
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:46,567
I'll take care of you.

458
00:25:48,067 --> 00:25:49,467
I won't leave you.

459
00:25:50,533 --> 00:25:52,533
I'll give you everything
you want.

460
00:25:55,300 --> 00:25:57,000
I'm begging you...

461
00:25:58,467 --> 00:25:59,867
leave Paolo.

462
00:26:01,467 --> 00:26:02,733
Forget about him.

463
00:26:04,900 --> 00:26:06,833
I don't want to see you
get hurt.

464
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:10,500
Marj, we belong together.

465
00:26:13,733 --> 00:26:15,033
I just...

466
00:26:17,933 --> 00:26:19,667
I hope you choose me.

467
00:26:30,467 --> 00:26:31,667
What did you say to Marj?

468
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:32,767
She suddenly started avoiding me

469
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:34,833
and won't reply to my messages.

470
00:26:34,967 --> 00:26:36,000
What did you tell her?

471
00:26:36,133 --> 00:26:37,200
What did I say?

472
00:26:37,333 --> 00:26:39,467
The truth! That she's just
another conquest to you.

473
00:26:39,600 --> 00:26:41,967
Your flavor of the month.

474
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:43,267
You just have to choose one.

475
00:26:43,433 --> 00:26:44,533
Either way, you win.

476
00:26:44,667 --> 00:26:45,700
So which one do you want?

477
00:26:45,833 --> 00:26:47,667
I didn't raise you
to be a loser.

478
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:49,200
Don't let your brother beat you.

479
00:26:49,333 --> 00:26:52,300
If there's anyone
I want you to marry,

480
00:26:52,433 --> 00:26:53,767
it's someone like Marj.

481
00:26:53,900 --> 00:26:55,567
Why are you telling me this?

482
00:26:55,700 --> 00:26:57,067
Sorry, I'm into someone else.

483
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:58,400
Marriage is serious.

484
00:26:58,533 --> 00:27:00,367
That's a lifetime commitment.

485
00:27:00,500 --> 00:27:02,667
Don't joke about something
like that.
